Dear RWO reviewer,

Jason, Yaron and I have cut a new alpha milestone of Real World OCaml, =
available at:
http://www.realworldocaml.org/alpha3/en/html/

Significant changes since the previous alpha:

- New preface and installation appendix giving more context about how =
the book should be read.
- Modules and functors chapters much more consistent.
- New object-oriented and imperative programming chapters.
- Over 200 comments addressed in Part I.  Keep them coming!

Part II (practical examples) and Part III (advanced topics) are *not* =
fully included in this milestone, and we request reviewers focus on the =
first part (although comments on the later half of the book are also of =
course welcome).

The plan for alpha4 in ~2 weeks (in addition to resolving your comments =
on alpha3) is to have a more complete Part II, and also to have chapters =
for the remaining structure of the book in place (although not fully =
complete).  This will let us also issue a PDF version (right now, the =
O'Reilly build process complains due to missing cross-references).

best regards,
Anil=

