Dear Real World OCaml reviewers,

The Alpha 4 milestone is now available online at:
http://realworldocaml.org/

Alpha4 completes Part I with the exception of the pattern matching =
chapter, and adds several new sections to Part II (JSON and the Command =
library) and Part III (half-finished runtime and garbage collection =
chapters).   Over 500 of your review comments have been addressed in =
this milestone, and our thanks for the excellent feedback to date.

We have changed our release scripts to stub out incomplete chapters =
instead of omitting them, which lets you see the structure of the =
overall book better (there are still some missing chapters, however).  =
This means that a PDF snapshot is also available via the website.  =
Although we prefer comments via the online system, if you find it more =
convenient to read it offline and scribble down notes, that's fine too.

We're aiming for the Async programming and runtime/garbage collection =
sections to be complete by the next milestone in a couple of weeks.

best,

Jason, Yaron and Anil=

